text\">In 2020, there were X number of people who maxed out their sentence lengths, meaning they were released on or after their mandatory release year, accounting for X% of releases from prison.</div>\n<br/>\nNo Data\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Unconditional vs Conditional Releases</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">In 2020, there were X number of people who were released conditionally from prison, meaning they were released from incarceration under specific conditions and supervision and often before they served their full sentence, accounting for X% of releases from prison.</div>\n<br/>\nNo Data\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Release Timing by Offense Type</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n::: {.panel-tabset}\n### Overview\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">In 2020, for people in prison for a new crime, X number of people (X%) were released from prison on their parole eligibility year.</div>\n<br/>\nNo Data\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Violent\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Property\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Public Order\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Drug\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Other\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Time Served by Offense Type</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n::: {.panel-tabset}\n### Overview\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">\nIn 2020, for people in prison for a new crime, X number of people (X%) served their full sentence length.\n<br/>\n<br/>\n</div>\nNo Data\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Violent\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Property\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Public Order\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Drug\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Other\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">No Data</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n</center>\n<br>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## Disparities\n\n<center>\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Descriptive Statistics</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\nRace, ethincity, age, and gender\n<br/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Relative Rate Index</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">The relative rate index (RRI) provides a measure of disparity in outcomes for different racial and ethnic groups by comparing the rates at which individuals of different races and ethnic groups experience incarceration. The rate for each specific racial and ethnic group is computed by dividing the population of interest within that group by the total state population for that particular group.</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">To calculate the RRI, the rate of each outcome of interest for individuals who are Black non-Hispanic and Hispanic any race, is divided by the rate at which the outcome occurs for individuals who are White. A RRI of 1 indicates no disparity. RRIs greater than 1 indicate the outcome occurs more frequently for individuals who are Black or Hispanic, and an RRI less than 1 indicates an outcome occurs less frequently than for individuals who are White.</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n::: {.panel-tabset}\n\n### First Time Offenses\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<div id=\"regular-text\">\nCompare parole eligibility rates or rates of release to parole for Black, White, and Hispanic individuals with similar first time offenses. For example, are Black people less likely to be released to parole on their parole eligibility date for drug-related convictions compared to White people?\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Time Served\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<div id=\"regular-text\">\nCompare time served for Black, White, and Hispanic individuals with similar sentence lengths and offenses.\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n### Sentence Length (not using)\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-ab2233172aaabc9c7f9c\" style=\"width:100%;height:650px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-ab2233172aaabc9c7f9c\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\"chart\":{\"reflow\":true,\"marginTop\":100,\"marginBottom\":80,\"spacingBottom\":80,\"width\":300,\"height\":300},\"title\":{\"text\":\"Black People, Non-Hispanic\"},\"yAxis\":{\"title\":\"\",\"type\":\"linear\",\"categories\":{\"0\":\" \",\"1\":\"1 = White<br>Reference Line\",\"2\":\" 